<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Hacker Assessor | <%= hacker.name %> Status</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1><%= hacker.name %> Status</h1>
    <h2>Missing Skills for <small><%= level.name %></small></h2>
    <ul>
    <% lackingSkills.forEach(function(skill) { -%>
      <li>
        <h3><%= skill %></h3>
        <p>JavaScript is the most popular programming language in the world. A proper understanding of it's good parts is desirable if you want to write maintainable, concise and usable code that will last forever.</p>
        <p>You don't have to be an expert in vanilla js but your understandig should be wide enough to be able to kick out jQuery.</p>
        <h4>Lectures</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/jquery/jquery/blob/master/src/ajax.js">jQuery</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.codecademy.com/tracks/javascript">Codecademy JavaScript Path</a></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    <% }); -%>
    </ul>
  </body>
</html>
